    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSION SHIFT LINKAGE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsection id="s13031" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5270" date="11/25/1997">
        <title>AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSION SHIFT LINKAGE</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <vendorgroup/>

                <vendor>Allison</vendor>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>1000</truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>4000</truckmodel>
                <vendcodegroup/>

                <vendcode>AT-542</vendcode>
                <vendcode>AT-545</vendcode>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The transmission shift control linkage used on the 1652SC, 4500, 4700, 4700LP, and 4900 models
                    with the Allison AT-542/545 transmission with dual neutral consists of either:
                </para>
                <para>The dash mounted shift lever, its mounting parts and the transmission cable located in the cab and
                    engine compartment (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303101">Figure 1</hotlnk>) and the transmission cable and transmission connecting
                    hardware mounted on the transmission (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303102">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1303101" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1303101" filename="../figg13/G1303101.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Dash-Mounted Shift Assembly</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. DASH-MOUNTED AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSION SHIFT CONTROL</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. SHIFT CONTROL MOUNTING BRACKETS</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. RUBBER GROMMET</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. EXTENSION CLIP, CABLE CLAMP, HEX BOLT, LOCKWASHER, HEX NUT</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. TRANSMISSION CABLE</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. PIPE HOSE CLIP</callout1>
                        <callout1>7. ACCELERATOR CABLE CLIP EXTENSION AND MOUNTING HARDWARE</callout1>
                        <callout1>8. TRANSMISSION CABLE GROMMET HOLE</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f1303102" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1303102" filename="../figg13/G1303102.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2. Transmission Cable and Transmission Connecting Hardware</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. TRANSMISSION CABLE</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. CABLE LOCK STRAP</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. PIPE CLAMP, HEX BOLT, LOCKWASHER, HEX NUT</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. EXTENSION CLIP</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. SHIFT CABLE BRACKET, SPACER</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. CABLE CLAMP, CAP SOCKET SCREWS, SPRING LOCKWASHER, WELD NUT, BRACKET BAR SPACER
                        </callout1>
                        <callout1>7. CONTROL CABLE SWIVEL, FLAT WASHER, COTTER PIN</callout1>
                        <callout1>8. LOCK OR HEX SPECIAL NUT</callout1>
                        <callout1>9. CONTROL LEVER PIVOT PIN, WASHERS, AND COTTER PIN</callout1>
                        <callout1>10. BRAKE CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                        <callout1>11. TRANSMISSION SHIFT LEVER</callout1>
                        <callout1>12. SHIFT CONTROL CABLE SWIVEL</callout1>
                        <callout1>13. HEX NUT, JAM</callout1>
                        <callout1>14. MODULATOR CABLE</callout1>
                        <callout1>15. TRANSMISSION SELECTOR SHAFT</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <para>OR</para>
                <para>The column shift lever, its mounting parts and the transmission cable located in the cab and
                    engine compartment (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303103">Figure 3</hotlnk>) and the transmission cable and transmission connecting
                    hardware mounted on the transmission (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303102">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1303103" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1303103" filename="../figg13/G1303103.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3. Column Shift Assembly</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. COLUMN-MOUNTED AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSION SHIFT CONTROL</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. RUBBER GROMMET</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. CABLE CLIPS</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. HEX BOLT, FLAT WASHER, HEX LOCK NUT</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. TRANSMISSION CABLE</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. PIPE HOSE CLIP</callout1>
                        <callout1>7. ACCELERATOR CABLE CLIP EXTENSION AND MOUNTING HARDWARE</callout1>
                        <callout1>8. TRANSMISSION CABLE GROMMET HOLE</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <para>The Allison AT-542/545 automatic transmission is equipped with dual neutral positions. The first
                    neutral position is the Park-Neutral position, consisting of a solenoid that will not allow shifting
                    of the transmission, and a mechanical brake attached to the propeller shaft. When this parking brake
                    is applied, it will not allow the propeller shaft to turn. The second neutral position is a standard
                    Neutral position which will allow the drive train to spin freely.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
